[4]
Date: Sun 7 Jul 2002
To: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Sun Star, Sun 7 Jul 2002 [edited]
<http://www.sunstar.com.ph/news/news_article_affiliate.php3?id=4682>

Philippines: Dengue Fever Affects 203 in Capiz Province
-------------------------------------------------------
ROXAS: Capiz Governor Vicente Bermejo on Fri 6 Jul 2002 said dengue cases
in the province are now alarming, with an increase this month in the number
of people affected. The dengue case [number] abruptly increased from 159 on
25 Jun 2002 to 203 as of Wed 3 Jul 2002. Bermejo, in a radio interview,
said the outbreak of the disease is now "very alarming" and urged the local
media to help disseminate information on how the public can avoid getting
bitten by mosquitoes, particularly the carriers of dengue virus. He added
that fogging activities in the affected areas are being conducted by the
health personnel with the assistance of the barangay officials.
City Mayor Antonio del Rosario also said the fumigation activities [had
been in progress already] in several elementary schools, the provincial
jail, and the slaughterhouse since 25 Jun 2002. The situation report
obtained by Sun Star Capiz from the office of the Governor indicates that
out of 203 victims of dengue fever: 10 are from Cuartero; 66 (the highest
number) from Dao ; 19 from Dumalag; 3 from Dumarao; 1 from Ivisan; 1 from
Jamindan; 6 from Maayon; 8 from Mambusao; 4 from Panay; 20 from Panitan; 2
from Pilar; 3 from Pontevedra; 6 from President Roxas; 5 from Sapian; 9
from Sigma; 7 from Tapaz; and 33 from Roxas City.
[Byline: Joel E. Capundan]
